# Loom workspace config (DO commit for team sharing)
# - config.json: Persistent terminal configurations (roles, themes, intervals)
# - roles/: Custom role definitions

# Claude Code settings
# - settings.json: Team-wide permissions (DO commit)
# - settings.local.json: Personal preferences (gitignored)
.claude/settings.local.json

# Dogfood symlink (issue #3311):
# When loom is installed *on* the loom source repo, `.claude/agents` is a
# symlink to `defaults/.claude/agents/` so the in-repo agent definitions
# always reflect the committed source-of-truth (no copy = no drift).
# Created by `./scripts/install-loom.sh --dogfood .` or auto-detected when
# installing into the loom repo itself.
.claude/agents

# Dogfood scoped symlink (issue #3682, supersedes the #3565 copy):
# When loom is installed *on* the loom source repo, `.claude/commands/` is a
# real directory whose `loom/` subdir is a SYMLINK into the shipped source of
# truth: `.claude/commands/loom -> ../../defaults/.claude/commands/loom`.
# A symlink cannot go stale; the earlier materialized COPY (#3565) drifted
# whenever `defaults/.claude/commands/loom/*.md` changed and caused a false bug
# report (#3665) when agents loaded outdated guidance.
# Scoping the link to the `loom/` subdir (not the whole `.claude/commands`
# directory) avoids #3565's failure mode: `.claude/commands/` itself stays a
# real dir, so a co-installed tool writing a SIBLING namespace
# (`.claude/commands/<ns>/foo.md`, e.g. the `repo` tool) writes into a real
# dir and never redirects through a symlink into loom's `defaults/` artifact.
# No tool other than loom's own installer/daemon writes the `loom/` namespace.
# Established by `link_dogfood_commands` in scripts/install/dogfood-commands.sh
# (mirrors the `.claude/agents` handling, scoped one level deeper).
# IMPORTANT: this ignore lives ONLY in loom's own committed .gitignore.
# Consumer repos keep `.claude/commands/loom/` TRACKED (real files, not a
# symlink), so it must NOT be added to the daemon's `update_gitignore` list in
# loom-daemon/src/init/post_init.rs.
.claude/commands

# Co-install hygiene (issue #3578, sibling of #3565):
# Loom ships no skills of its own (`defaults/.claude/skills/` does not exist),
# so `.claude/skills/` in the live tree is a pure destination for co-installed
# tools that write `.claude/skills/<ns>/…` (e.g. `repo` writes
# `.claude/skills/repo/SKILL.md`). Ignoring it keeps a foreign tool's files
# from being accidentally staged into loom's tree by `git add -A`.
# IMPORTANT: this ignore lives ONLY in loom's own committed .gitignore. It must
# NOT be added to the daemon's `update_gitignore` list in
# loom-daemon/src/init/post_init.rs, so consumer repos keep any skills they author TRACKED.
# If loom ever ships its own skills, materialize/dogfood them like
# `.claude/commands/loom/` (out of scope here).
.claude/skills

# Skill routing local overrides (untracked, user-specific)
.loom/config/skill-routes.local.json
.loom/*.log
.loom/*.sock
.loom/logs/
